      "raceComments": "{\"comment\":\"8. RING is a Paul Abela-trained newcomer by Bernardo out of Zita. Start all important and will need some luck getting across from the wide draw. Strong market watch advised but profiles nicely for this. 3. STACEY DEVERE jumps from box 3 again after finishing third (22.41) last time at Shepparton over 390m. Harder here but expected to measure up. 1. LAND OF ANGER put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at Horsham behind Maximum Sunny (23.82) in a Maiden. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Must be included in calculations. 2. DON'T LOOK can feature with the right run.\",\"runners\":[8,3,1,2],\"exclusive\":false}",
